This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with Human Action Recognition using 3D sensors. It also involves modeling sequential data, which suggests it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Variational Bayes framework, which is a common technique in the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
